title: Helped our new budgie learn to trust us!
content: Our little parakeet loves this treat!  He was very traumatized when we got him, but with the help of this millet he soon learned to come right to us and eat out of the palm of our hands.  We’ve had him a little over a month and now he trusts us and seems to feel very secure.  Our biggest problem is being disciplined in not allowing him to eat too much, as it’s so tempting when he’s so dang cute!!  Highly recommend this product. It came very fresh and packaged well.
author: Cynthia Griffith
product: Kaytee Spray Millet for Birds, 12 Count (Pack of 1)

title: Color was gone
content: I always buy this time and I was wondering  why my bird didn't eat it cause it was dried out color was not looking fresh.
author: Chevelle
product: Kaytee Spray Millet for Birds, 12 Count (Pack of 1)

title: Birds won't touch it and usually love it.
content: I have been using this product for years.  The last order my birds won't eat it.  I smelled it and it smells like hay.  I usually use this for a treat.  They love millet but not this batch.
author: Happy Shopper
product: Kaytee Spray Millet for Birds, 12 Count (Pack of 1)

title: My cockatiel loves it.
content: This is something I use as a treat for my bird. He knows what he's going to get if I ask him if he wants a treat. I always keep it on hand. I also use it as extra food if I need to be gone for a couple days. I know he won't run out of food.
author: Danette Kulzer
product: Kaytee Spray Millet for Birds, 12 Count (Pack of 1)

content: Poor quality. The seed is very old and dried up. The sprays look old and not desirable for my rooster to eat.
